{{BLP sources|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox person | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1978|5|27|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax, Nova Scotia]], [[Canada]] | occupation = Actress | years_active = 1989âpresent }} '''Cindy Sampson''' (born May 27, 1978) is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[film actress|film]] and [[television actress]].
==Biography== {{Empty section|date=August 2010}}
== Career == === Films === Her biggest film role was as Zoe Ravena in ''[[Live Once, Die Twice]]''. For the film ''The Shrine'', now in post-production, Sampson was required to watch a specific list of horror films in preparation for the role.<ref name="BD1">{{cite web |url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/article/600 |title=The Shrine: A Visit to the Set in Toronto |last=Pereira |first=Mike |publisher=Bloody Disgusting |accessdate=2009-11-18}}</ref> She appeared in the lead role of the Crime thriller film [[The Factory (film)|The Factory]].<ref>[http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/20635 First Images from John Cusack Thriller 'The Factory'!]</ref>
=== Television === Sampson's other appearances include ''[[Reaper (TV series)|Reaper]]'', ''[[Supernatural (TV series)|Supernatural]]'', ''[[The Last Kiss]]'',''[[Being Human (North American TV series)|Being Human ]]'', ''[[Footsteps (2003 film)|Footsteps]]'', ''[[Proof of Lies]]'', ''[[Pretty Dead Flowers]]'' and ''[[Swamp Devil]]''. She also portrayed Sandra MacLaren in ''[[Rumours (TV series)|Rumours]]''.
Sampson appeared in Season 3 of ''Supernatural'' as the character Lisa Braedon ( guest star), she appeared in the episode The Kids Are Alright. She reprised the role for the episode Dream a Little Dream of Me after showrunner Eric Kripke could not get the rights to use the character Jason Voorhes.
Sampson's character was brought back in Season 5 at the last minute due to the show being renewed for a sixth season, she appeared in the episode 99 problems and Swan Song. Sampson has thus far appeared in 11 episodes of the current series of the show. She appeared in the episode Mannequin 3: The Reckoning alongside Jensen Ackles, Jared Padelicki and Nicholas Elia.
Her final appearance was in the episode Let it Bleed alongside Jensen Ackles, Jared Padelicki and Nicholas Elia. Sampson's latest film projects Charlie Zone and Long Day Gone are in post production.
